============================================================
Problem 1b: Find constant a for independence
============================================================

Parameters:
σ²_X = 2
σ²_Y = 3
ρ = -0.666667
Cov(X,Y) = ρσ_Xσ_Y = -1.6329931619

For aX + Y and X + 2Y to be independent, we need Cov(aX + Y, X + 2Y) = 0

Cov(aX + Y, X + 2Y) = a·Var(X) + 2a·Cov(X,Y) + Cov(X,Y) + 2·Var(Y)
                    = a·σ²_X + (2a+1)·Cov(X,Y) + 2·σ²_Y

Setting equal to 0:
a·σ²_X + (2a+1)·Cov(X,Y) + 2·σ²_Y = 0
a(σ²_X + 2·Cov(X,Y)) = -(Cov(X,Y) + 2·σ²_Y)
a = -(Cov(X,Y) + 2·σ²_Y) / (σ²_X + 2·Cov(X,Y))
  = -(-1.6329931619 + 2·3) / (2 + 2·-1.6329931619)
  = -4.3670068381 / -1.2659863237
  = 3.4494897428

============================================================
EXACT SYMBOLIC COMPUTATION:
============================================================
Cov(X,Y) = -2*sqrt(6)/3 = -2*sqrt(6)/3
a = -(Cov(X,Y) + 2σ²_Y) / (σ²_X + 2Cov(X,Y))
  = (-6 + 2*sqrt(6)/3)/(2 - 4*sqrt(6)/3)
  = 1 + sqrt(6)

Numerical value: 3.4494897428
Direct calculation: 3.4494897428
Difference: 1.78e-15

============================================================
VERIFICATION:
============================================================
Cov(aX + Y, X + 2Y) = a·σ²_X + (2a+1)·Cov(X,Y) + 2·σ²_Y
                    = 3.4494897428·2 + (7.8989794856)·-1.6329931619 + 2·3
                    = 0.000000000000000e+00
Check: |Cov| < 1e-8: True

Monte Carlo verification (n=1000000):
Sample Cov(aX + Y, X + 2Y) = -7.2733068304e-03
Sample Corr(aX + Y, X + 2Y) = -6.7585367358e-04
Check: |Cov| < 1e-2: True

============================================================
FINAL ANSWER:
============================================================
a = 1 + sqrt(6)
  ≈ 3.4494897428
